        <p class="metadata">Posted by Martin Mayer (martin.mayer) on 2008-12-13T06:46:34.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>Hi Vincent, in Reference Manual you can learn, that default analyzer doesn't treat numbers as part of terms ([<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.search.lucene.charset.html#zend.search.lucene.charset.default_analyzer">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a>]). You can use another analyzer this way:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer::setDefault(
    new Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer_Common_Utf8Num()
);
</code></pre>

<p>You can find more analysers in Zend/Search/Lucene/Analysis/Analyzer/Common/. Remember also to build index using specified analyser.</p>

        </div>
